<HistoricalDocument xmlns="http://example.com/historicaldocument">
  <Metadata>
    <Language>German</Language>
    <WritingDirection>ltr</WritingDirection>
    <PhysicalDescription>Parchment, single folio side, good condition.</PhysicalDescription>
    <Description>List of names, likely attendees or parties involved in a legal or administrative matter.</Description>
    <Script>Latin</Script>
  </Metadata>
  <Page>
    <Header>
      <PageNumber>73</PageNumber>
    </Header>
    <Body>
      <List type="unordered">
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch zuͦ dem ersten Myn herˀn graff Albrecht vō</Line>
          <Line>Anhalt</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch her Ludwig Lantgraff von Lichtenberg</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch groff Ott von Hennenberg</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch groff Bernhart von Regenstein</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch groff Gottfried von Hohenloch</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch groff Gebhart von Mansfeld</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch groff Ludwig von Isenburg</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch her Gotthalc von Bless <Addition>et</Addition> Bedpanchˀn</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch her Hans von Turgow</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch Jerg Bappenheim</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch her Buppin von Stein wz vorhin Ritter</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch Lucz von Rotenhan</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch Jerg von Waldenfels</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch Hylbrand von Thuͦngen</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch Jerg von Slieben</Line>
        </Item>
        <Item>
          <Line>Jch Henÿn quast</Line>
        </Item>
      </List>
    </Body>
  </Page>
</HistoricalDocument>
